## Codebase Discoveries
- The lead.md file uses Mustache-style `{{TRACKER_CLI}}` and `{{QUALITY_GATE_INLINE}}` placeholders that are interpolated by `ov sling` at agent spawn time. Don't write literal `{TRACKER_CLI}` or assume the file is read as-is at runtime.
- The lead's overlay (path at `{{INSTRUCTION_PATH}}`) is generated by `ov sling`, NOT by greenhouse. Greenhouse writes the SPEC at `.greenhouse/<seedsId>-spec.md`. The coordinator dispatched by greenhouse reads the spec and feeds parts of it into `ov sling --spec ...` when spawning the lead. So the lead reading the dispatch spec relies on the coordinator including the labels in the spawned spec — which is the dispatcher.ts default behavior.

